# cursor-supabase-app Project Rules

## Tech Stack Context
- Data visualization app using React 18 + Vite + Recharts + Supabase
- JavaScript only — never suggest TypeScript migration

## Data Access
- All database queries go through the `useSupabase` hook
- Never fetch Supabase directly in components

## Chart Components
- All chart components live in `src/components/charts/`
- Standard props: `data` (array), `xKey` (string), `yKey` (string), `title` (string), `color` (string)
- When adding a new data visualization: add it to Dashboard.jsx AND export from charts index

## Configuration
- ML API base URL: `import.meta.env.VITE_ML_API_URL` — never hardcoded
- Supabase table/column names: from env vars or constants — never hardcoded strings

## Dependencies
- Never install new npm packages without asking the user first

## Components
- All components must be functional components with hooks — no class components
- CSS in `.module.css` files colocated with components — no inline styles except dynamic values
- Keep components under 150 lines; split into smaller components if needed

## Data Fetching
- Always handle loading, error, and success states in components that fetch data
